  "body": "First thing, follow the instructions https://hackmd.io/@4_PBxu6jQtO7qASCOn0H6w/Skx96BPsK to run mergemock and erigon together. **Note:** you need to run first rpcdaemon+erigon and then run the mergemock after.\r\n## Logs\r\nErigon:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1254\" alt=\"Schermata 2022-01-04 alle 19 53 16\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29233688/148109263-a66340b0-996b-4562-81d2-5060f9f8bed5.png\">\r\n\r\nMergeMock:\r\n<img width=\"1258\" alt=\"Schermata 2022-01-04 alle 19 55 09\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29233688/148109419-ac11de26-07ea-4161-8a8e-d54d94dffdf5.png\">\r\n\r\nThere were gaps beetwen slot 4 and 8 so block number 5 is at slot 8, this bug only appears when `--proposer` flag is enabled, so it is related to mining on proof-of-stake. However, i see that the beacon chain is receiving a correct GasLimit computed by Erigon(`fmt.Println` the GasLimit in GetPayloadV1) but then gives off a block with 1000000 GasLimit",
